		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The "EFA" solution is to add a USB controller and some sort of CPLD that can write to the PRG and CHR buses in order to rewrite the flash chips.
<br />
<br />The "SuperCard" solution, reminiscent of the FDS, is to add a 512 KB PRG RAM, a 256 KB CHR RAM, a CF or SD slot connected to a CPLD, and a small KB flash chip to hold a bootloader that loads a program from CF or SD.
<br />
<br />In each case, the CPLD would probably act as the mapper.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
